          "username": "a.sreekumar"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-01-27 17:31:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Hey Rashmi, based on Ram's comments in my review, see\n> \n> https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/policy/drools-pdp/+/126786\n> \n> let's try to reach agreement on how the counts:\n>   \n> 1 - should there be commonality between same counts with the name?\n> \n> 2 - if so, what should be the strategy for naming common things among PDPs provided that there would be differences.\n> \n> I understand the recommended practices that you would model the monitored thing with one object and particular aspects with labels, see the references in my review.   Under these guidelines, 1 counter would be used instead of 3.\n> \n> minus-1'ing your review and mine until we resolve on this.\n\nProbably better to identify and decide on the names and then keep it in some common place like https://github.com/onap/policy-common/blob/master/utils/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/common/utils/resources/MessageConstants.java so that it can be reused across all components",
